		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.01]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=XColbyX&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>just a quick over view (as i&nbsp;&nbsp;know little bout them as well) you trade beastmen seals to the guy in port jeuno to get an orb. go to the burning circle and trade and select your fight. as for party... ask linkshell, shout in jeuno, but in windy you may get some volunteers. <br><br>typically when doing a group bcnm everyone has their own orb and you do it 3-6 times in a row (how ever many people are doing it) and everyone keeps their own drops. luck of the draw i guess on what you get. <br><br>or if you REALLY REALLY REALLLLLLY trust the people you pt with one can sell everything from all 3-6 drops and then split up the gil between. if you wanted one of those drops you would have to forfeit your gil (according to ah price) when the payout comes. also if you are the one selling the items make sure to inform your pt about the jeuno tax and u about the little bit more gil you'll receive to make up for selling it. (happened to me once and i decided not to argue and just took the loss. 500k spell means a 50k charge &gt;&lt; ) <br><br>hope this helps and others feel free to add or correct</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Name : Colby<br>Server : Remora<br>Home : San Doria<br>Lvls : 42RNG | 30MNK | 26NIN | 20RDM | 16THF | 13WAR | 7WHM/BST/BRD | 5BLM/SMN | 3DRG | 1PLD/DRK/SAM<br>Crafts : 55 Cooking | 27 Woodworking</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
